<class module="videoDriver" runtimeProfile="wb" qualifiedName="com.tridium.videoDriver.ui.holdDownButton.px.BHoldDownPxButton" name="BHoldDownPxButton" packageName="com.tridium.videoDriver.ui.holdDownButton.px" public="true">
<description>
Works with a BHoldDownPxBinding to periodically invoke an action, fire&#xa; a topic, or set a property value as the main mouse button is held down.&#xa; &#xa; Also works with the BHoldDownPxBinding to invoke an action, fire a topic,&#xa; or set a property value as the main mouse button is released.&#xa; &#xa; This is accomplished by using a topic named &#x27;mouseActivity&#x27;. When the&#xa; main mouse button is pressed, the mouseActivity topic is fired with&#xa; a BHoldDownPxButton.MOUSE_DOWN_EVENT. Then, as/if the main mouse button&#xa; is held down, the &#x27;mouseActivity&#x27; topic is fired periodically with a&#xa; BHoldDownPxButton.MOUSE_DOWN_EVENT until the main mouse button is released.&#xa; When the main mouse button is release, this fires the mouseActivity&#xa; topic with a BHoldDownPxButton.MOUSE_RELEASE_EVENT.&#xa; &#xa; Then the BHoldDownPxBinding child of this button (configured by the &#xa; integrator on the PxEditor) detects the &#x27;mouseActivity&#x27; topic with the&#xa; BHoldDownPxBinding.MOUSE_DOWN_EVENT and invokes the action, fires the&#xa; topic, or sets the property that is identified by the mouseDownSlot&#xa; on the binding.&#xa; &#xa; Likewise, the BHoldDownPxBinding child of the button (configured by the&#xa; integrator on the PxEditor) detects the &#x27;mouseActivity&#x27; topic with the&#xa; BHoldDownPxBinding.MOUSE_RELEASE_EVENT and invokes the action, fires&#xa; the topic, or sets the property that is identified by the&#xa; mouseReleaseSlot on the binding.
</description>
<tag name="@author">lperkins</tag>
